external_knowledge:
- "bustling beacons of intellectual fervor" refers to schools with high student enrollment;
- "harboring over two thousand eager minds" means the student enrollment is more than 2000;
- "boasting an average SAT score above the golden mark of 1500" indicates the average SAT score is greater than 1500;
- "arranged in order from the most populous to the least" is the descending order of student enrollment.

- "educational beacons" refers to schools;
- "shone brighter than the standard" implies average SAT math scores greater than 700;
- "above the 700-point threshold" means SAT math scores higher than 700.

sql:
SELECT school_id, MIN(student_enrollment) AS min_enrollment
FROM enrollment
GROUP BY school_id;

SELECT schools.*
FROM schools
WHERE school_id = (
  SELECT school_id
  FROM enrollment
  WHERE student_enrollment = (
    SELECT MAX(student_enrollment)
    FROM enrollment
  )
);
